# Frontend Rules

## Stack
- React with Vite only
- Tailwind CSS utility classes only
- shadcn/ui for all UI components
- Never use plain CSS files, CSS modules, or inline styles
- Never use HTML form elements, use React controlled components

## Component rules
- Components are small and single-purpose
- Props are typed with TypeScript interfaces or PropTypes
- State managed with useState or useReducer only
- No external state management libraries unless explicitly approved

## Streaming
- All query responses use a custom useSSE hook
- Never use plain fetch without streaming support for query endpoints
- Tokens append to message state as they arrive
- Show loading indicator while waiting for first token

## Required components
- UploadZone: drag and drop, polls GET /ingest/status/{job_id} every 2s
  until status is ready or failed, shows status transitions visually
- ChatWindow: streaming chat, text appears token by token
- MessageBubble: renders user and assistant messages differently
- SourceCard: document name, page number, chunk preview, image thumbnail
  if source was an image or chart
- WorkspaceSelector: dropdown to switch between company workspaces

## API integration
- Base URL from environment variable VITE_API_URL
- Never hardcode localhost URLs in component code
- Handle 4xx and 5xx errors with friendly user-facing messages
- Never show raw error objects or stack traces to the user